alse,"rule_id":"USDPA-006","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-007","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-008","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-009","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-010","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-011","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-012","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-013","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-014","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-015","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-016","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-017","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-018","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-019","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-020","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-021","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-022","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-023","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-024","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-025","rule_version":"1.0.0"}],"findings":[{"description":"Used but not defined: Disclosing Party, One Million Dollars.","document_position":1944,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1960,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1944,"text":"Disclosing Party"},"explanation":"Title-Case phrases in a contract usually signal a defined term. When they aren't defined, readers must guess at the intended meaning. Either define them or use lowercase if the term is intended in its ordinary sense.","id":"STRUCT-006-s1-1944","recommendation":"Add a definition for each genuinely defined term, or change the casing if the phrase is being used in its ordinary sense.","rule_id":"STRUCT-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Undefined Title-Case terms: 2"},{"description":"The following references do not resolve to any section: Section 8(a), Section 5, Section 7.","document_position":4806,"excerpt":{"end_offset":4818,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":4806,"text":"Section 8(a)"},"explanation":"A broken cross-reference can mean the referenced section was renumbered or deleted, or that a section reference was made up. Either way the reader has no way to follow the citation.","id":"STRUCT-007-s1-4806","recommendation":"Update each broken reference to point to the correct section, or delete it if it is no longer applicable.","rule_id":"STRUCT-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Unresolved cross-references: 3"},{"description":"The survival clause exists but does not name: IP ownership / assignment, indemnification.","document_position":1807,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2558,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1807,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidential given the nature of the information an"},"explanation":"Survival language is what keeps sticky obligations alive after a contract terminates. A survival clause that doesn't expressly enumerate the present-in-document confidentiality / IP / indemnity obligations creates ambiguity at the moment those obligations matter most — post-termination, when the contract has already ended.","id":"TEMP-012-s1-1807","recommendation":"Add explicit named references to the missing obligation(s): IP ownership / assignment, indemnification. Standard drafting names every sticky section by number or category in the survival clause.","rule_id":"TEMP-012","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival clause does not name 2 sticky obligations"},{"description":"The contract does not state what happens upon termination.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no effect-of-termination clause)"},"explanation":"An effect-of-termination clause spells out the rights and obligations that survive, the return or destruction of materials, and the wind-down rules.","id":"TERM-005-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No effect-of-termination clause detected"},{"description":"The document does not state where disputes must be brought.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no venue clause)"},"explanation":"Without a venue clause, default venue rules apply (in federal court, 28 U.S.C. § 1391). A clear forum-selection clause avoids ambiguity.","id":"CHOICE-003-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-28-usc-1391","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"28 U.S.C. § 1391 (venue generally)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/28/1391"}],"title":"No venue / forum clause detected"},{"description":"The indemnifying party shall not settle any claim in a manner that imposes liability on the indemnified party without th | EACH PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY TO THE OTHER PARTY FOR ALL CLAIMS ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO THIS AGREEMENT SHALL NOT | The aggregate liability cap in Section 8(a) shall not apply to: (i) either party's breach of its confidentiality obligat | THIS MUTUAL EXCLUSION OF CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES SHALL NOT APPLY TO BREACHES OF CONFIDENTIALITY OR INDEMNIFICATION OBLIGAT","document_position":4297,"excerpt":{"end_offset":4462,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":4297,"text":"The indemnifying party shall not settle any claim in a manner that imposes liability on the indemnified party without the indemnified party's prior written consent."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-4297","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 4"},{"description":"INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES","document_position":5187,"excerpt":{"end_offset":5243,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":5187,"text":"8. Limitation of Liability. (a) Aggregate Liability Cap. EACH PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY TO THE OTHER PARTY FOR ALL CLAIMS ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO THIS AGREEMENT SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL FEES PAID OR PAYABLE BY CUSTOMER TO VENDOR IN"},"explanation":"A waiver of consequential, special, incidental, and punitive damages is standard in commercial contracts. The waiver should be mutual unless deliberately asymmetric.","id":"RISK-007-s1-5187","rule_id":"RISK-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Consequential damages waiver present"},{"description":"commercial general liability insurance with limits of at least One Million Dollars ($1,000,000","document_position":5709,"excerpt":{"end_offset":5803,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":5709,"text":"9. Insurance. During the term of this Agreement, Vendor shall maintain at its own expense: (a) commercial general liability insurance with limits of at least One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence and Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000) in the aggregate; (b) professional liability / errors and omissions insurance"},"explanation":"Insurance levels should match the deal size and risk. Common minimums are $1M per occurrence CGL and $2M E&O for services contracts.","id":"RISK-010-s1-5709","rule_id":"RISK-010","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Insurance requirements stated"},{"description":"Indemnity clause appears to be missing: notice, settlement consent.","document_position":3149,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3157,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3149,"text":"7. Mutual Indemnification. (a) Vendor Indemnification. Vendor shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Customer and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any third-party claim, action, or proceeding arising out of or relating to any allegation that the"},"explanation":"A complete indemnity clause specifies (a) the timeline and form for notice of a claim, (b) which party controls defense, and (c) whether settlement requires consent.","id":"RISK-011-s1-3149","rule_id":"RISK-011","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Indemnity procedural elements missing: notice, settlement consent"},{"description":"confidentiality obligations no less protective than this Agreement. These mutual confidentiality obligations shall survive termination of this Agreement for three (3) year","document_position":2385,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2556,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2385,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidentia"},"explanation":"Typical post-termination confidentiality terms run 3–5 years for general information, with a perpetual duty for trade secrets. Verify the term matches the sensitivity of the information.","id":"RISK-014-s1-2385","rule_id":"RISK-014","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Confidentiality term length stated"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a Definitions section or any inline-defined terms.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no definitions located)"},"explanation":"Most non-trivial contracts capitalize defined terms and either set them out in a Definitions section or define them inline (\"X\" means …). Their absence is not by itself a problem, but downstream rules that check for use of specific defined terms will be skipped.","id":"STRUCT-004-s1-0","rule_id":"STRUCT-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"No defined terms detected"},{"description":"Provisions are stated to survive termination.","document_position":2500,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2519,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2500,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidentia"},"explanation":"A survival clause names the obligations that outlast termination — typically confidentiality, indemnity, payment obligations accrued before termination, and choice of law.","id":"TEMP-006-s1-2500","rule_id":"TEMP-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival clause present"},{"description":"Survival clause does not appear to include: indemnity, payment, governing law.","document_position":2500,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2519,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2500,"text":"5. Confidentiality. Each party (as \"Receiving Party\") shall hold in strict confidence all non-public information of the other party (as \"Disclosing Party\") designated as confidential or that reasonably should be understood to be confidentia"},"explanation":"Typical surviving obligations include confidentiality, indemnity, accrued payment obligations, and governing law. Missing any of these is common and worth confirming.","id":"TEMP-007-s1-2500","rule_id":"TEMP-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival list may be missing categories: indemnity, payment, governing law"}],"playbook_id":"mutual-nda","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to msa-vendor-deep","result_hash":"16e4df8f0757e98f9ded875cbc9c809ea4f076d6a4659c39323ffeda4a0f8715","source_file":{"name":"msa-vendor-deep-minimal-pass.txt","sha256":"d423800f8586a52aa3f4a34495d9fac291500cb92bce3887ebf898e3f84637df","size_bytes":1},"version":"0.1.0"}